BICKNELL v. SPIER. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. April 2, 1894.) Action by Henry G. Bickneil against Gilbert M. Spier, Jr., as receiver of the Vertical Tube Boiler Company. A judgment in favor of plaintiff was affirmed (27 N. Y. Supp. 38G), and defendant moves for leave to appeal to the court of appeals. Denied.

Argued before DALY, C. J., and BISCHOEF and PRYOR, JJ.

John C. O’Connor, for appellant. Bullard & Shannon, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

The question of law for review is not stated, nor can it be discovered in the moving papers. White v. Balta (herewith decided) 28 N. Y. Supp. 3. Motion denied, with $10 costs.
